      <p>I grew up in Houston, Texas and graduated with a Bachelor of Science in Industrial Design from the University of Houston, with a minor in Architecture. I started out designing physical products — housewares, exhibits, prototypes — before moving into digital product and UX.</p>
      <p>That background shapes how I work: I lead groups, hold a sustained vision for collaborative efforts, and bring ideas from concept to manufacturing — or from research to shipped product. I like solving complex problems with simple, effective solutions and connecting people with beautiful experiences.</p>
      <p>For the last several years I've worked as an Experience Lead and Lead UX Designer at Merkle — shaping strategy, running workshops, and coaching designers across complex, multi-workstream engagements. Before that I was the sole UX designer on a pricing tool now used across Shell's global chemicals business.</p>
      <p>When I'm not designing, you'll usually find me working on cars — fixing anything from a flat tire to a blown piston.</p>
      <p class="quote">"Every project is more challenging than the one before, and that's what pushes me forward. I love design's ever-changing environment — this is what makes me happy."</p>
